      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"predicting\" doesn't explain why the things being posted are things I haven't even typed out or even shared with anyone. it's like the version of me online is living a life that's more \"me\" than i actually am. i feel like the person using my accounts is the real me and i'm just... the shadow. if an AI can mirror me this perfectly, at what point does the digital version actually become the primary identity? it feels like i've already been overwritten.",
